    "Moreover, among the 744 key-sentences, 1,109 relations were annotated, indicating an average of 1.5 relationships between TF and diseases per key-sentence.",
    "Furthermore, as shown in Table 1, among the 1,109 relation annotations, the \"Treatment of Disease\" relationship accounts for the largest proportion at 83.3% (924), followed by \"Association\" at 12.8% (142).",
    "The \"Cause of Side-effect\" relationship represents 2.7% (30), while \"Negative\" stands at 1.2% (13).",
    "technical Validation inter-annotator agreement.",
    "In the process of building the TFDR corpus, two annotation phases are involved manual annotation by annotators: Initial annotation, which involved annotating pre-annotated abstracts, and annotation revision, which entailed re-annotating by reflecting the resolutions of review meeting."
